North Korea Is Banned From 2015 Women’s World Cup for Doping Offenses

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-08-25T17:40:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/north-korea-is-banned-from-2015-women-s-world-cup-for-doping-violations.html
Soccer ruling body FIFA banned  North
Korea  from the next Women’s  World Cup  after five of its players
failed drug tests at this year’s tournament in Germany,  Pok Sim Jong, Myong Hui Hong, Un Byol Ho and Un Hyang Ri
were banned from the sport for 18 months and Jong Sun Song for
14 months, FIFA said in a release.  A doctor from the country’s soccer association, Jong Ae
Nam, was found guilty of violating anti-doping rules and
suspended for six years.  FIFA also fined the North Korean soccer association
$400,000. The next Women’s World Cup is in Canada in 2015.  North Korea failed to advance out of the group stage of the
tournament in  Germany , held in June and July.  Colombian goalkeeper Yineth Varon, suspended June 28
after a positive out-of-competition drug test, was banned for
two years, FIFA said.  FIFA didn’t specify in the release what banned substances
were involved.  To contact the reporter on this story:
